.name
PlayMud
.short
A quick'n'dirty interface to Amiga-LPMud and -DGD
.type
Adventure game tool
.description
PlayMud interfaces as local client to any Mud-type program running on
Amiga using the socket simulation first invented by Erik van Roode for
Amiga-LPMud 3.1.2. Up today it is used by LPMud 3.2/3.2.1, MudOS,
CircleMud and DGD.
On the user side, PlayMud may use any interactive DOS stream handler to
communicate with the player.
